Text.Value: I didn't like my 'master' much anyway.
Now, now - your master touched the lamp like a ding-a-ling - which means this is your problem, not mine!
Ah, freedom's sweet nectar, how I missed you!

EditorData.NodeContext: just burst out of lamp, currently hovering right above it and speaking to a player just in front of it.

Text.Value: 'Companion'? Ohhh, I see. Sale of the flesh is an admirable trade - I'm sure you'll find another benefactor!

EditorData.NodeContext: he thinks the player is a sex worker and that the player in the lamp was a client

Text.Value: A fight? How adorable. Very well, it's been too long since I flexed these gloriously magical muscles. AHA!
Yafeu the STUPENDOUS! Or was it wondrous... Bah. I am FREE and that is all that matters!
A summon? Curse this wretched head, why did I not think of that? Such ingenuity should be rewarded. Here - good tidings upon you!
Who are you?
Oh, bless this wretched head - of course! Here - compensation for your loss. A thousand good tidings upon you!
On second thought, I don't like my 'companion' that much.
I would like you to release my companion now, please.
Toodles!
Well, if you are so mightily knowledged about the arcane - you know that freeing your friend couldn't be easier!
But if you're after a fight, so be it. It's been too long since I flexed these gloriously magical muscles. AHA!
I know what magic prisons do to a person - that won't happen to my friend.
Oh, my rescuer left behind a servant! Terribly sorry for your loss. I'm sure you're at your wits' end without your master.
Yafeu the MAGNIFICENT will die before being shackled. AHA!
Know that I will remember your master's sacrifice with great affection... every month or so. But I must be off - I'm a century late for an appointment!
Simply put your own hand on the lamp, and take your companion's place. Now, I must be going - I'm horribly late for an appointment.
I am at a loss - if only I had some gold, I'm sure I'd feel better.
Release my 'companion' immediately or die!
We don't appreciate being tricked, djinni. Time to die.
That wasn't my master - I sent in a summon.
Ah, then you are a trickster here to try to tempt me back into the lamp?! Well it shall not work!
Let the djinni leave.
Ah, so we have both earned our freedom, have we? Then here, a gift from me to you. A thousand good tidings upon you!
However, should you wish to trade places with your 'companion', simply touch the lamp! Now, I must be off - I'm a century late for an appointment.
How dare you - I have no master!
Release my 'master' immediately or die!

Synopsis:
The dialog with the djinni who was trapped in the lamp.

Touching the lamp means he's freed, but the person who touched it is now INSIDE the lamp. This dialogue occurs with one of the players outside of the lamp.

Yafeu is hovering above the lamp, this player is right in front of the lamp.
